description:
&lt;p&gt;Bank Band 5 Immunisation Nurses&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CSH Surrey is a not-for-profit community services provider with a passion for helping people live the heathiest lives they can in their communities. We focus every day on making a difference for the people we care for - adults, children and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Everything we do, we do with CARE, because we care about our patients and clients, our colleagues and our partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We care with&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;ompassion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We take&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;ccountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We show&lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt;espect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We deliver&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;xcellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of CSH Surrey’s People Strategy with strong focus of our workforce’s wellbeing, we are currently looking for experienced and committed Bank Band 5 Immunisation Nurses who can support our immunisation team to deliver the staff Flu immunisation programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced and motivated Nurse to join our established Immunisation Team offering the Flu programme to our 1500+ workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to possess a good understanding of the public health role and have worked in community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills and an ability to work independently as well part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will offer the right candidate a warm and friendly welcome with a full induction programme and ongoing support, training and development to further advance your skills and career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working under the supervision of Lead Peer &lt;strong&gt;Lead Peer Vaccinator&lt;/strong&gt; Nurse, you will be supported to develop&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your knowledge and skills relating to immunisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our practitioners work toward our shared purpose:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caring about their clients, seeking to make the support that colleagues receive as beneficial and positive an experience for them as possible&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compassionate and reflective, appreciating the value of research and best practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Courageous in innovation and always ready to have a go&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel the same, we look forward to receiving your application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact our Lead Peer Vaccinator Nurse BALLINGALL, Rosemarie (CSH SURREY) r.ballingall@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews: wc 16th November&lt;/p&gt;
